<p>The first step in reaching AHERA compliance is to find and review your school's existing Management Plan. Answer the following questions about the AHERA Management Plan for your school to find out what AHERA resources will benefit you most. </p><ul>
	<li>Is the Management Plan current?</li>
	<li>Does the Management Plan include 6 month periodic surveillance documents?</li>
	<li>Does the Management Plan include a record of asbestos awareness training for all of the maintenance and janitorial staff working in your school? </li>
	<li>Has your school designated a person to ensure the requirements of AHERA are properly implemented? Does the Management Plan include a record of asbestos training for your AHERA designated person?</li>
</ul>
<p>If you answered "yes" to the questions above the following resources may be helpful in maintaining AHERA compliance. </p>
<ul>
	<li><a title="AHERA Compliance Inspection Checklist" href="http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/WorkArea/linkit.aspx?LinkIdentifier=id&amp;ItemID=8589978847">AHERA Compliance Inspection Checklist</a> <span class="small">(PDF, 63KB)</span> </li>
<li><a title="AHERA Asbestos Management Plan: Self Audit Checklist for Designated Persons" href="http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/WorkArea/linkit.aspx?LinkIdentifier=id&amp;ItemID=8589979603">AHERA Asbestos Management Plan: Self Audit Checklist for Designated Persons</a> <span class="small">(PDF, 321KB)</span> </li>
</ul>
<p>If you answered "no" to the questions above start learning about AHERA and what you need to comply. The following helpful resources make the steps you need to take to comply with AHERA clear and easy to understand.</p>
